quran[25]{c,v,t}:
  19,16,"Mention in the Book the story of Mary, when she withdrew from her family to a place toward the east"
  19,17,"and secluded herself from them. We then sent to her Our Spirit, who appeared to her in the shape of a perfect human being"
  19,18,"She said, \"I seek refuge from you in the Merciful, [leave me alone] if you are God fearing"
  19,19,"He said, \"I am only the Messenger of your Lord, [who says,] 'I will give you a son endowed with purity"
  19,20,"She said, \"How can I have a son when no man has touched me and I have not been a promiscuous woman"
  19,21,"He said, \"It will be so. Your Lord says, 'It is easy for Me, and We will make him a sign to people and a mercy from Us. The matter is already determined"
  19,22,"So she conceived him, and she withdrew with him to a remote place"
  19,23,"Then the pains of childbirth drove her to the trunk of a palm tree. She said, \"Oh, I wish I had been dead and forgotten before all this"
  19,24,"But a voice called to her from below, \"Do not grieve; your Lord has provided a stream beneath you"
  19,25,"Shake the trunk of the palm tree toward you; it will drop ripe, fresh dates to you"
  19,26,"So eat and drink and be satisfied and say to anyone you may see, I have made a vow of silence to the Lord of Mercy and I will not talk to anyone today"
  19,27,"Then she went back to her people, carrying him. They said, \"Mary, you have done an unthinkable thing"
  19,28,"Sister of Aaron, your father was not a bad man, nor was your mother a loose woman"
  19,29,"She pointed to him. They said, \"How can we speak to a child in the cradle"
  19,30,"[Jesus] said, \"I am the servant of God. He has given me the Book and made me a prophet"
  19,31,And He has made me blessed wherever I am and directed me to pray and to give charitable gifts as long as I live
  19,32,"and to be full of kindness toward .mother, and He has not made me domineering or rebellious"
  19,33,"And [God's] peace was upon me the day I was born and the day I will die and it will be upon me the day I am raised alive"
  19,34,"Such is Jesus, the son of Mary - the Word of Truth about which they are in dispute"
  19,35,"It does not befit God to have a son; may He be exalted in His glory! When He decides on something, He simply says to it, \"Be!\" and it is"
  19,36,"[Jesus continued]: \"God is my Lord and your Lord, so worship Him. That is a straight path"
  19,37,"Then, the sects differed among themselves [concerning the nature of Jesus], so woe to those who reject the truth when they witness that awesome Day"
  19,38,"How [clearly] they will hear and see on the Day they will come before Us. Today, however, they are in clear error"
  19,39,"Warn them of the Day of Regret, when everything will have been decided; and [yet], they are heedless, and they do not believe"
  19,40,"It is We who will inherit the earth and all those on it, and to Us they will be returned"